        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "what happens if there are two or more different implementations of jre on same platform?",
        "body": "<p>I have two jre versions installed on my system (1.3 &amp; 1.5) and i am trying to some java applet programs through internet explorer. All i wanted to know is that how will the web browser select which version of jre to use when the applet program is executed.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 20093931,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "applet",
            "jvmti"
        ],
        "score": 1,
        "accepted_answer_id": 20094066,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 81
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/psP1R.jpg?s=256",
            "account_id": 3106191,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 2628911,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2628911/sandhu-santhakumar",
